  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic implant wear credibility assessment (NC-4 clean package)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA-based contact stress and polyethylene wear prediction in a total knee replacement (TKR) tibial insert under gait loading conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case contact mechanics and wear accumulation for a Class II orthopedic device at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 Complete profile. All 13 factors addressed; 9 assessed with requiredLevel and achievedLevel populated; 4 scoped-out with documented rationale. Decision: Accepted.",
